.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.TOTALSQUAREDINTERFRAMEDELAY" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.totalSquaredInterFrameDelay \-
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats: totalSquaredInterFrameDelay property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]totalSquaredInterFrameDelay\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the sum of the
square of each inter\-frame delay between consecutively rendered frames.
It is recorded after each frame is rendered.
.PP
The inter\-frame delay variance be calculated from
\f[CR]totalInterFrameDelay\f[R], \f[CR]totalSquaredInterFrameDelay\f[R],
and \f[CR]framesRendered\f[R], according to the formula:
\f[CR](totalSquaredInterFrameDelay \- totalInterFrameDelay\(ha2/ framesRendered)/framesRendered\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The property is undefined for audio streams.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A positive number.
